<h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">What's Next</h1>

<p class="govuk-body-l">
  Simply Readable was built by Swindon Borough Council and is now adopted by councils across the UK and internationally. Here are resources to help you take the next step.
</p>

<hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break--visible">

<h2 class="govuk-heading-l">The people behind it</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Simply Readable was developed by Swindon Borough Council's Emerging Technology team, led by <strong>Sarah Pena</strong> (Head of Emerging Technology) under <strong>Philip Murkin</strong> (Chief Digital Officer). The Easy Read feature was co-created with the council's <strong>"Experts by Experience of a Learning Disability"</strong> focus group &mdash; residents with learning disabilities who tested and shaped every aspect of the tool.
</p>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  The tool is now adopted by Edinburgh, Newport, Southampton, West Berkshire, and councils in France. It has been recognised by AWS, i.AI, Socitm, Digital Leaders, and the Local Government Association.
</div>

<hr class="govuk-section-break govuk-section-break--l govuk-section-break--visible">

